Synaxis Upgrade Instructions
────────────────────────────

From X3 or older Synaxis:
  1. Back up your .db files
  2. Build and install the new version
  3. After starting, run: /msg OpServ REBINDALL
     This binds all new commands.

Database Compatibility:
  Synaxis 2.2.0 is backward-compatible with X3 database files.
  Existing accounts, channels, and settings are preserved.
  Argon2id passwords are used for new registrations; MD5
  passwords from older installs are accepted and auto-migrated.

New in 2.2.0:
  - Native TLS for S2S uplink connections
  - NickServ: IDENTIFY, DROP, LOGOUT, GROUP, GLIST, ALIST,
    REGAIN, INFO, CERT, SUSPEND, UNSUSPEND, ACCESS, CONFIRM,
    UPDATE commands
  - OpServ: AKILL, NETINFO, IRCOPS, HELPERS, STAFF, FORBID
  - Channel prefix modes +q (owner) and +a (protect)
  - GCC 15 clean compilation (0 errors, 0 warnings)
  - Python 3 support (mod-python)
  - Argon2id + libsodium password hashing
  - Proper make install (bin/, etc/, share/, var/)
